name: Seoul Coffee n Grill, Sangeh
address: Jl. Raya Sangeh, Sangeh, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1: Delicious food for a small price. Nice place next to the rice fields
review 2: Friendly place. Coffee was okayish, definitely needs some better dialling in on the grinder. Mango juice a bit too much ice, not enough mango. Little plastic stirrer in the juice was dirty and needs better cleaning. Morning Glory Vegetables was good as was the fruit platter. View is fantastic, so for a quick stop I'd highly recommend it if you keep in mind shortcomings on the coffee and so on. Place seems new so I'm sure it'll get sorted out.
review 3:
I am writing this review based on my experience on March 25th, 2023, hoping that it is still relevant today.

After swimming at Tirta Arum Swimming Pool, drinking and buying tuak at Tuak Bejidong, I continued to Seoul Sangeh for a meal. I saw that the reviews were quite good, so I ordered a burger here. However, perhaps the burger is not the recommended dish here, as I found it to be quite ordinary compared to others at the same price.

What can be enjoyed at this restaurant, which I think is more like a cafe, is the beautiful view (rice fields) and the spacious area, which could be suitable for events. It also appears to have relatively good lighting at night (assuming the lights are placed there).

Overall, I will come back here to try other dishes, especially the pizza.
review 4: Found this gem on the way to Sangeh. Lovely. It's in the middle of rice paddy. Has beautiful view. I can spend hours eating and drinking coffee. Very peaceful at daytime. I can see farmers working. The price is also cheap. Great place to chat with friends or family.
review 5: Was not too bad tho, my second time there. But compare with the 1st time when they're opening I think much more happening and more food options as I remember. Too bad, now they downgraded they're menu. Anyway still the best place for eat and chill if you passed into these area.

name: Warung Sawah Sawah
address: Jl. Raya Sangeh, Sangeh, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352, Indonesia
review 1:
Good quality local food for a very reasonable price. Very authentic fish restaurant in Sangeh area next to a huge rice field.

The fish was crispy and tasty, came with steamed veggie, rice and ice tea for 55k.

I will be back trying out other dishes!
review 2: Like this restaurant, unique and cozy.. About taste standard.. But everything ok.. Good rice fields view... Mini playground that's make all complete. Good place to bring our kids..
review 3: This is best resto everything is there so great delicious food ,coffee very strong value money pizza soooo delicious i love order here ,really recommended for everyone ,they have also booze ,wine ,beer ,spirite i bought many from.lakmsi Breakfast pizza and bar i can order anytime they open 24 hours  i love it
review 4: Nicely located beside a rice field and the first food was nice. So try it.
review 5: Really one of the best places I've eaten in Bali so far, this place deserves more recognition then it gets. This restaurant has got it all. Amazing view over the rice paddies, relaxing atmosphere, unbelievable food and competitive pricing. We ordered the Chicken Sweet and Sour and Chicken w. Balinese sause. 10/10 would recommend.
